    "text": "The number isn't wrong, but it also isn't the whole truth. On the data side, 77% is well supported: HRV is 58 ms against your 30-day mean of 51.6 ms \u2014 a genuinely large lift given your usual swing is under 3 ms \u2014 resting heart rate is 60 bpm, just below your 61.1 bpm baseline, and you slept a healthy 8.2 hours. Nothing there is glitchy. But the score only sees physiology; it can't see mood, motivation, stress, or a heavy week of life, and feeling flat is real information the tracker doesn't capture. The practical move: start your planned session with a long, honest warm-up. If the flatness burns off in ten minutes, as it often does on high-recovery days, proceed as planned. If it doesn't, downshift to an easy session without guilt \u2014 you get the final vote, not the score.",
